INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (4,1,'whatsaysyou','interesting.knowledge@gmail.com','http://whatsaysyou.wordpress.com','122.58.198.109','2011-10-04 09:56:21','2011-10-04 09:56:21','Wow, I didn\'t know that October is reading month and now I like that idea. The reading habit can be imparted on a child once it is done at a young age as well as making reading as part of life\'s routine as something fun. The public library is a great place to start for any parent who wants to instil the reading habit in a child. Secondly, I believe when parents love to read, they do beget kids who have a passion for reading. I maybe in my late twenties but I love reading as long as I could remember having my bedtime stories as a child or going to the library with my mum.',0,'1','','',0,0),(5,1,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','74.210.28.48','2011-10-04 12:38:44','2011-10-04 12:38:44','This is definitely one habit to grow as early as possible. For October being reading month see www.nationalbook.org/nbm.html \n\nThe public library is beautiful, free and a cosy environment for budding book-lovers to be nurtured. And yes, parents who love to read tend to have kids who love to read, once they get over any fluency blocks that they may be experiencing. Like you, my mom always read to me, read lots of books herself and took me to the library regularly to re-stock my rapidly diminishing supply as I gobbled up book after book.',0,'1','','',4,0),(6,15,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2011-10-10 20:15:12','2011-10-10 20:15:12','I hope many people take advantage of this blog...discovering the wonders of Kumon education.  :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(7,15,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','74.210.28.48','2011-10-10 20:18:01','2011-10-10 20:18:01','I hope so too, Kathy! Thanks for dropping by!',0,'1','','',6,0),(8,15,'Shavon Gallwas','Cabrar@hotmail.com','http://www.getconstructionsoftware.com','112.187.142.26','2011-10-17 07:12:27','2011-10-17 07:12:27','I found this post to be very to the point. When I have some time later I\'m going to write a more detailed comment sharing my feelings.',0,'1','','',0,0),(9,15,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','74.198.87.51','2011-10-20 20:28:11','2011-10-20 20:28:11','Thanks, I look forward to it, Shavon. Sorry, wordpress had decided your comment was spam so I had to unspam it.',0,'1','','',8,0),(10,15,'michael jackson family tree','u.freliek@web.to','http://www.come-and-read.com/Art/642584/31/Our-Pegasus-Thunderbolt-Transfer-File-Transfer-Data.html','109.73.79.2','2011-11-02 07:23:00','2011-11-02 07:23:00','<a href=\"http://www.come-and-read.com/Art/642584/31/Our-Pegasus-Thunderbolt-Transfer-File-Transfer-Data.html\" title=\"michael jackson family tree\" rel=\"nofollow\">michael jackson family tree</a> \nDo you have a spam issue on this site; I also am a blogger, and I was wondering your situation; many of us have developed some nice procedures and we are looking to exchange techniques with other folks, why not shoot me an email if interested.',0,'1','','',0,0),(11,32,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2011-11-05 23:41:54','2011-11-05 23:41:54','Unoccupy your sofa!  That\'s funny.  Interesting quote by Ursula Le Guin.  Are you joining the Occupy Movement in Hamilton?',0,'1','','',0,0),(12,32,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','74.210.28.48','2011-11-05 23:47:34','2011-11-05 23:47:34','I am up to my ears in Occupy Hamilton, being on both Media and Communications/Outreach, attending two General Assemblies a week and tracking and responding to countless emails, tweets and FB messages related to Occupy. Wouldn\'t be so involved if I didn\'t think all this time was well spent. There is tremendous potential here to change a lot of things many had grown hopeless over...',0,'1','','',0,0),(13,32,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2011-11-05 23:49:18','2011-11-05 23:49:18','Good for you, Nicole.  You ARE up to your ears.  Chris and his wife, Seunghye, went to the San Diego Occupy.',0,'1','','',12,0),(14,32,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','74.210.28.48','2011-11-06 00:03:48','2011-11-06 00:03:48','What did they think of it? And yes, I\'m above my ears if you count the choir concerts on Nov 13, 25-27 and Dec 3, the awards ceremony at the centre on Nov 22, all the association activities and everything else :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(15,32,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2011-12-03 18:58:23','2011-12-03 18:58:23','Just stoppin\' back to see if you had written anything new on your blog.  But I\'ll bet you\'re way too busy!  December 3rd is today--good luck and have fun!  (Chris and Seunghye enjoyed being there, supporting it, but I don\'t think they were there more than once or twice.)',0,'1','','',14,0),(16,32,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://gravatar.com/kumonofhamiltonwestend','74.210.28.48','2011-12-03 22:10:08','2011-12-03 22:10:08','Yes, life has been even more hectic than I expected :) leaving in half an hour for the concert and after that is a party with colleagues of Robert\'s. Looking forward to blogging over the next weeks when it is quieter (I hope! still pretty busy until the 21st)',0,'1','','',0,0),(17,37,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2012-01-02 13:45:05','2012-01-02 13:45:05','This is very beautiful, Nicole.  What a year it was for you!  So many changes.  I wish you your deepest heart\'s desire in 2012.  I think you already know many of my 2012 thoughts!  Love to you, and New Year\'s hugs.',0,'1','','',0,0),(18,37,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://gravatar.com/kumonofhamiltonwestend','74.210.28.48','2012-01-02 13:46:43','2012-01-02 13:46:43','Yes, just read your day 2, my dear! New Year\'s hugs back, holding you close in my heart as you continue your quest.',0,'1','','',0,0),(19,37,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2012-01-19 01:06:39','2012-01-19 01:06:39','Just pausing at your hearth to see if you\'ve posted anything new.  Can you believe we\'re 18 days into 2012 already?  Sometimes it feels like it\'s been forever.  My, time passes quickly.  Hope you are well!',0,'1','','',0,0),(20,37,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://gravatar.com/kumonofhamiltonwestend','74.198.87.127','2012-01-19 18:41:10','2012-01-19 18:41:10','Yup, I definitely should have written another blog by now! I have all kinds of good topics too. I just never catch up with my necessary work first... Thanks I am well if rather overwhelmed :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(21,44,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2012-02-05 23:17:09','2012-02-05 23:17:09','Loved reading this blog, Nicole.  Very interesting!  I used to love math.  It felt really fun to follow the instructions to get to the appropriate results.  Really loved Algebra.  However, these days would have to re-learn everything all over again...',0,'1','','',0,0),(22,44,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','74.198.87.92','2012-02-07 15:59:47','2012-02-07 15:59:47','I\'m so glad you enjoyed it Kathy, and that you used to love Math. It\'s true, you have to re-learn things if you are out of the loop too long, but it\'s a bit like learning to ride a bicycle :)',0,'1','','',21,0),(23,44,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.110','2012-03-06 21:28:44','2012-03-06 21:28:44','Hi Nicole!  Just seein\' if you\'ve been bloggin\'...',0,'1','','',0,0),(24,44,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://gravatar.com/kumonofhamiltonwestend','174.88.12.16','2012-03-07 13:10:28','2012-03-07 13:10:28','Thanks, Kathy!',0,'1','','',0,0),(25,87,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.83','2013-03-12 23:36:39','2013-03-12 23:36:39','Makes it clearer to me!  :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(26,87,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','76.67.13.24','2013-03-12 23:38:04','2013-03-12 23:38:04','Excellent! :) Thanks for stopping by...',0,'1','','',25,0),(27,242,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.83','2013-03-21 23:51:00','2013-03-21 23:51:00','What a delightful story!',0,'1','','',0,0),(28,242,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://gravatar.com/kumonofhamiltonwestend','184.148.56.150','2013-03-22 13:41:43','2013-03-22 13:41:43','So glad you enjoyed it, Kathy!',0,'1','','',0,0),(29,1300,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.83','2013-03-30 17:14:58','2013-03-30 17:14:58','\"And the fire and the rose are one\".  Oh YES, Nicole!',0,'1','','',0,0),(30,1300,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','184.148.44.42','2013-03-30 19:19:51','2013-03-30 19:19:51','Amazing, isn\'t it, Kathy?',0,'1','','',0,0),(31,1318,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.204','2013-05-07 22:29:52','2013-05-07 22:29:52','How did the clean up go, Nicole?  Forgot to ask you!  Hope you are doing well.  And Hamilton, too.',0,'1','','',0,0),(32,1318,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://gravatar.com/kumonofhamiltonwestend','184.148.41.166','2013-05-07 23:43:06','2013-05-07 23:43:06','Thanks it was fun! A long story but we are very much looking forward to next year!',0,'1','','',0,0),(33,1340,'Kathy','kdrue@up.net','http://upwoods.wordpress.com','206.51.119.204','2013-07-23 11:23:19','2013-07-23 11:23:19','This looks like a wonderful time, Nicole!  Thank you for sharing all about it.  (I hope some of your fellow Kumon folks will get to see your blog.)  How wonderful that a 12 year old student had enough confidence to emcee the event--that delighted me.  Your photos provide a lovely illustration of the conference.  Really enjoyed coming over here to read this today.',0,'1','','',0,0),(34,1340,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','76.67.15.30','2013-07-23 13:59:27','2013-07-23 13:59:27','Thanks, Kathy, you gave me the good idea of sharing my blog with my colleagues. I have already Facebooked it on my centre page, because that is what I do. I still need to tweet it. I intend to continue to blog about the past few weeks. So much has happened - I want to share about my wonderful trip to Scotland and the conferences in Washington DC and Baltimore.',0,'1','','',0,0),(35,1432,'jinazmistry','jinaz_mistry@yahoo.co.in','http://taarrcim.wordpress.com','27.106.62.238','2013-09-12 13:49:28','2013-09-12 13:49:28','We humans have innate infinite powers waiting to be unleashed. Once we overcome our list of excuses, the cant\'s become cans.',0,'1','','',0,0),(36,1432,'kumonofhamiltonwestend','hamiltonwestend_on@ikumon.com','http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com','64.229.2.198','2013-09-12 14:36:27','2013-09-12 14:36:27','Yes, our potential is astonishing. Just think of all we could do ...',0,'1','','',0,0),(37,1583,'Susan Storm','susiekiltz@gmail.com','http://psychologyjunkie.com','184.155.212.147','2015-10-29 20:00:01','2015-10-29 20:00:01','Hello! I just wanted to say thank you for reading my article, and I\'m so glad you enjoyed it! I truly hope it will be a help to children, parents, teachers, or anyone who can use it. I was very honored that you appreciated it, and I\'m looking forward to checking out more of your posts.',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/40.0.2214.91 Safari/537.36','',0,0);
