s nulla nec neque eleifend consectetur in nec nisi. Vestibulum luctus justo ut lacus semper vestibulum. Nulla tempus erat sit amet dui interdum iaculis. Fusce quis sollicitudin lorem.</p>\r\n[spacer]\r\n[spacer]\r\n[/column]\r\n[/row]','Home','','inherit','open','closed','','96-revision-v1','','','2014-10-03 02:04:26','2014-10-03 02:04:26','',96,'http://1pixeldesign.com/dev/wordpress2/96-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(211,1,'2013-11-26 17:41:39','2013-11-26 17:41:39','<h3>Kumon of Hamilton West End</h3>\r\n[circleimage has_hovericon=false hovericon=fa-chevron-circle-right class=\"alignright\" imgurl=http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/001-e1436885039303.jpg] Centre Director and Instructor, Nicole Smith, has 20 years experience running Kumon centres in Montreal and Ontario, working in both French and English. She has through her Kumon centres helped many hundreds of students over these years develop in their math, English, and learning skills, including her own three children, all of whom are successfully pursuing careers and university studies in Montreal.\r\n\r\nOur staff:\r\n\r\n1) Our receptionist, Holly Fraser, has worked the longest of all the staff at the centre, and has become very knowledgeable about the Kumon programs and how best to help children get a good start and make excellent progress at the centre.\r\n\r\n2) Our Early Learners assistant, Roshaya Rodness, worked for several years at a Montreal centre with emergent readers and is highly effective at facilitating the development of each student according to his or her particular needs.\r\n\r\n3) Math and Reading staff: Elizabeth Selinger, Sara Manzoor, Ananya Sharma, Nuzhat Rafique, and Clair Macauley-Newcombe.\r\n\r\n[spacer]\r\n<h3></h3>','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about-us','','','2015-10-21 02:18:29','2015-10-21 02:18:29','',0,'http://revitalizesolutions.ca/?page_id=211',0,'page','',0),(1520,1,'2015-07-14 17:37:29','2015-07-14 17:37:29','<h3>Kumon of Hamilton West End</h3>\r\n[circleimage has_hovericon=false hovericon=fa-chevron-circle-right class=\"alignright\" imgurl=http://dev.1pixeldesign.com/wordpress2/wp-content/themes/1pixel/images/default-image-545x545.jpg]Owner-Operator and Instructor, Nicole Smith, has 20 years experience running Kumon centres in Montreal and Ontario, working in both French and English. She has through her Kumon centres helped many hundreds of students over these years develop in their math, English, and learning skills, including her own three children, all of whom are successfully pursuing careers and university studies in Montreal.\r\n\r\nOur staff:\r\n\r\n1) Our receptionist, Holly Fraser, has worked the longest of all the staff at the centre, and has become very knowledgeable about the Kumon programmes and how best to help children get a good start at the centre.\r\n\r\n2) Our Early Learners assistant, Roshaya Rodness, worked for several years at a Montreal centre with emergent readers and is highly effective at facilitating the development of each student according to his or her particular needs.\r\n\r\n3) Math and Reading staff: Elizabeth Selinger, Shyamalee Randeni, Sara Manzoor, Ananya Sharma, Nuzhat Rafique, and Clair Macauley-Newcombe.\r\n\r\n[spacer]\r\n<h3></h3>','About Us','','inherit','open','closed','','211-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 17:37:29','2015-07-14 17:37:29','',211,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/211-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1544,1,'2015-09-22 13:41:48','2015-09-22 13:41:48','\"How early is early learning in Kumon? If my child is 2 or 3, is she too young for Kumon?\"\n\nThe only way to know for sure if your child is ready for Kumon is to bring her or him in for a free placement test at the centre. Generally, we have found 2 year old children do not usually have the patience to sit and study daily for at least 15-20 minutes, and advise that you begin around 3 or 4, depending on the personality and patience of your child with focused seat work.\n\nIf a child is not quite ready, we will usually recommend to re-test in 3-6 months. Often by that time, the child has become eager and prepared to begin learning Kumon.\n\nLevels 7A and 6A of the Reading program, and 6A and 5A of the Math program, are designed to help young children not only develop strong pre-reading and basic numeracy skills, but also begin to develop study skills that will stand them in good stead throughout their life - good pencil hold, good posture, fine-motor skills, neatness of presentation, concentration/focus and the facility to study steadily instead of being constantly distracted, and so on.\n\nIn 5A through 3A of Reading and 4A and early 3A of Math, students prepare for the big transition to the main study area of Kumon where they will be developing more and more independent study skills at a pace comfortable for each child.\n\n&nbsp;','Early Learners','','inherit','open','closed','','1515-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-22 13:41:48','2015-09-22 13:41:48','',1515,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1515-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2013-10-15 18:56:25','2013-10-15 18:56:25','<div class=\"row fix-nest \">\r\n    <div class=\"medium-6 columns\">\r\n        [text* your-name placeholder \"Name\"]\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"medium-6 columns\">\r\n        [text company-name placeholder \"Company Name\"]\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row fix-nest \">\r\n    <div class=\"medium-6 columns\">\r\n        [tel your-phone placeholder \"Phone number\"]\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"medium-6 columns\">\r\n        [email* your-email placeholder \"Email\"]\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row fix-nest \">\r\n    <div class=\"medium-6 columns\">\r\n        [text job-title placeholder \"Job title\"]\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"medium-6 columns\">\r\n        [text service-interested placeholder \"Service you are interested in\"]\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row fix-nest \">\r\n    <div class=\"medium-12 columns\">\