king habits. I also believe Kumon makes children feel confident in their abilities and lets them \'own\' their own process.\"\r\n\r\n\"After having my children enrolled in Kumon for two years, I have come to the conclusion that all kids should do Kumon from the earliest age possible. The benefits are so great that no parent should have any doubts about enrolling his/her children in Kumon when they are still young.\"\r\n\r\nTo read our success stories, go <a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/testimonial/\">here</a>. For other success stories from centres all over North America, visit<a href=\"http://www.Facebook.com/Kumon\" target=\"_blank\">Kumon North America\'s Facebook page</a>.','Success Stories','','inherit','open','closed','','1120-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 15:03:08','2015-09-22 15:03:08','',1120,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1557,1,'2015-09-22 15:09:43','2015-09-22 15:09:43','Our Math programis carefully designed to help support your child in study at the \"just-right\" level for him or her, beginning with a comfortable, confident starting point, to prepare for success in high school, university and beyond.\r\n\r\nEach level has 200 worksheets. Practice is provided based on the individual needs of the child, and the number of worksheets used daily is also individualized.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A-4A are the Early Learner levels, where students develop basic numeracy skills through 50. For more details about these levels, see\r\n\r\nLevels 3A-B are the addition and subtraction levels. This is where most Kumon students begin their studies with us, developing a strong foundation of addition and subtraction fact memorization, and the ability to do vertical addition and subtraction with regrouping at a mastery level.\r\n\r\nLevels C-D are the multiplication and division levels, providing students with very strong mental calculation skills in short and long multiplication and division, as well as teaching them how to convert improper fractions to mixed numbers and how to reduce fractions.\r\n\r\nLevels E-F are the operations with fractions and decimals levels which are so necessary for success with algebra and calculcus. We do the thorough groundwork in fractions most students lack through schoolwork.\r\n\r\nLevels G-I are the basic algebra levels, which also cover negative numbers, exponents, and graphing skills, the core concepts of grades 7 through grade 11.\r\n\r\nLevels J-O are the advanced algebra and calculus levels.\r\n\r\nLevels X are the enrichment modules for high school students studying in levels J-O who wish to delve deeper into topics like vectors, matrices, probability and statistics.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Math','','inherit','open','closed','','1504-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 15:09:43','2015-09-22 15:09:43','',1504,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1504-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1542,1,'2015-09-22 13:35:19','2015-09-22 13:35:19','<h3>Kumon of Hamilton West End</h3>\r\n[circleimage has_hovericon=false hovericon=fa-chevron-circle-right class=\"alignright\" imgurl=http://dev.1pixeldesign.com/wordpress2/wp-content/themes/1pixel/images/default-image-545x545.jpg] Centre Director and Instructor, Nicole Smith, has 20 years experience running Kumon centres in Montreal and Ontario, working in both French and English. She has through her Kumon centres helped many hundreds of students over these years develop in their math, English, and learning skills, including her own three children, all of whom are successfully pursuing careers and university studies in Montreal.\r\n\r\nOur staff:\r\n\r\n1) Our receptionist, Holly Fraser, has worked the longest of all the staff at the centre, and has become very knowledgeable about the Kumon programs and how best to help children get a good start and make excellent progress at the centre.\r\n\r\n2) Our Early Learners assistant, Roshaya Rodness, worked for several years at a Montreal centre with emergent readers and is highly effective at facilitating the development of each student according to his or her particular needs.\r\n\r\n3) Math and Reading staff: Elizabeth Selinger, Sara Manzoor, Ananya Sharma, Nuzhat Rafique, and Clair Macauley-Newcombe.\r\n\r\n[spacer]\r\n<h3></h3>','About Us','','inherit','open','closed','','211-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 13:35:19','2015-09-22 13:35:19','',211,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/211-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1119,1,'2015-06-09 21:43:18','2015-06-09 21:43:18',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','1119','','','2015-09-24 00:45:04','2015-09-24 00:45:04','',0,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/?p=1119',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1541,1,'2015-09-22 13:31:57','2015-09-22 13:31:57','<h2>Introduction</h2>\r\nI have nearly 20 years experience as an extensively trained and certified professional instructor. I will guide your children through their work while also providing direction, support and encouragement. Through careful observation of each student and his or her work, I create a personalized at-home study plan which I am constantly updating in response to each student\'s actual results on a class by class basis, as well as in response to my assessment of progress being made at home.\r\n\r\nI have learned through working with hundreds of children of all ages and a wide range of abilities and personalities that it is vital that each assignment be completed and corrected in a timely manner to 100% within a designated time frame. Thus parents are strongly encouraged to check their children\'s work daily, and ensure corrections are done quickly and comfortably. Close adherence to the Kumon method has helped my students increase study skills, math and/or English skills as well as their self-confidence, and thus they become more self-reliant.\r\n\r\nI have a true passion for education and an earnest desire to help children succeed. I have seen how Kumon can transform lives for the better and know that while it demands a significant family commitment, it is well worth the investment of time and money.\r\n\r\n<section class=\"subSec\">\r\n<h2><span id=\"cphContent_ctl00_listSection_labelSectionTitle_1\">Biography and Background</span></h2>\r\n[circleimage imgurl=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/001-e1436885039303.jpg\" align=right has_hovericon=false]As a franchise owner and instructor , I ran learning centres in both French and English in the Outremont and West Island areas of Montreal before moving to Hamilton in the fall of 2010.\r\n\r\nHaving successfully guided hundreds of students in the Kumon method, I have made more than a career of it. It is a way of life for me. I have noticed that many people come to Kumon after trying different tutoring approaches and becoming discouraged with the lack of results. It is amazing how much of a difference Kumon can make to children\'s learning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nAnother passion of mine is singing in classical concert choirs. I currently sing with Voces Animaeand the choir at the Anglican Church of the Ascension on John and Charlton, directed by John Laing - see his site at <a href=\"http://www.johnlaing.ca/\">http://www.johnlaing.ca/</a>. I am one of the main soloists and cantors at the church, and often play the flute there. I have formerly sung with Masterworks of Oakville.\r\n\r\nFinally, I am a member of the Hamilton Chamber of Commerce and the Canadian Federation of Independent Business (CFIB).\r\n\r\n</section>','About The Instructor','','inherit','open','closed','','1113-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 13:31:57','2015-09-22 13:31:57','',1113,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1113,1,'2015-06-09 21:21:41','2015-06-09 21:21:41','<h2>Introduction</h2>\r\nI have nearly 20 years experience as an extensively trained and certified professional instructor. I will guide your children through their work while also providing direction, support and encouragement. Through careful observation of each 