 organist and composer John Laing - see his site at <a href=\"http://www.johnlaing.ca/\">http://www.johnlaing.ca/</a>','About','','inherit','open','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 15:21:41','2015-07-14 15:21:41','',2,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1506,1,'2015-07-14 15:14:19','2015-07-14 15:14:19','I (Nicole Smith) am the owner/operator of the Kumon Math and Reading Centre of Hamilton West End in Ontario, Canada. I have been a Kumon franchisee for nearly 20 years and have now been in Hamilton nearly 5 years running my Kumon centre.\r\n\r\nWe celebrated our annual Awards ceremony for all our students on Tuesday, April 28, 2015, during our regular class hours of 3:30 to 7:00 p.m.\r\n\r\nNow that summer is here, we have a full range of fun activities lined up for our students:\r\n\r\n1) Summer Reading Challenge - the two students who read the most books in July and August, and write at least one paragraph on each book, in two different age categories (7 and under, 8 and up), will win the opportunity to purchase a book of their choice, up to a value of $30.\r\n\r\n3) Summer Photo Contest - see <a href=\"http://kumonsummer.ca\">kumonsummer.ca</a>for details\r\n\r\n4) Weekly Raffles - variety of prizes available in centre - twice-weekly attenders have many opportunities to win all summer long!\r\n\r\n5) Level Up!Students who are enrolled in participating centres during July, August and/or September will receive ballots for entry into a contest to win one of three $20 Chapters gift cards at the centre. Students can earn additional ballots by moving on to a new level and by reaching or maintaining a spot on the Advanced Student Honour Roll.There will also be two Grand Prize Winners in each Branch who will each receive an iPad Mini provided by Kumon Canada!\r\n\r\nI am a member of the Hamilton Chamber of Commerce and the Canadian Federation of Independent Business (CFIB), and I enjoy singing as a soloist/cantor and member of the choirs Voces Animae and the Anglican Church of the Ascension, under the direction of renowned organist and composer John Laing - see his site at <a href=\"http://www.johnlaing.ca/\">http://www.johnlaing.ca/</a>','About','','inherit','open','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 15:14:19','2015-07-14 15:14:19','',2,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1116,1,'2015-09-24 15:59:51','2015-09-24 15:59:51','<h2>Introduction</h2>\nI have nearly 20 years experience as an extensively trained and certified professional instructor. I will guide your children through their work while also providing direction, support and encouragement. Through careful observation of each student and his or her work, I create a personalized at-home study plan which I am constantly updating in response to each student\'s actual results on a class by class basis, as well as in response to my assessment of progress being made at home.\n\nI have learned through working with hundreds of children of all ages and a wide range of abilities and personalities that it is vital that each assignment be completed and corrected in a timely manner to 100% within a designated time frame. Thus parents are strongly encouraged to check their children\'s work daily, and ensure corrections are done quickly and comfortably. Close adherence to the Kumon method has helped my students increase study skills, math and/or English skills as well as their self-confidence, and thus they become more self-reliant.\n\nI have a true passion for education and an earnest desire to help children succeed. I have seen how Kumon can transform lives for the better and know that while it demands a significant family commitment, it is well worth the investment of time and money.\n\nTo find out more about our Math program, click<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/math/\">here.</a>\n\nTo find out more about our Reading program, clickhttp://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/reading/\n\n<section class=\"subSec\">\n<h2><span id=\"cphContent_ctl00_listSection_labelSectionTitle_1\">Biography and Background</span></h2>\n[circleimage imgurl=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/001-e1436885039303.jpg\" align=right has_hovericon=false]As a franchise owner and instructor , I ran learning centres in both French and English in the Outremont and West Island areas of Montreal before moving to Hamilton in the fall of 2010.\n\nHaving successfully guided hundreds of students in the Kumon method, I have made more than a career of it. It is a way of life for me. I have noticed that many people come to Kumon after trying different tutoring approaches and becoming discouraged with the lack of results. It is amazing how much of a difference Kumon can make to children\'s learning.\nAnother passion of mine is singing in classical concert choirs. I currently sing with Voces Animaeand the choir at the Anglican Church of the Ascension on John and Charlton, directed by John Laing - see his site at <a href=\"http://www.johnlaing.ca/\">http://www.johnlaing.ca/</a>. I am one of the main soloists and cantors at the church, and often play the flute there. I have formerly sung with Masterworks of Oakville.\n\nFinally, I am a member of the Hamilton Chamber of Commerce and the Canadian Federation of Independent Business (CFIB).\n\nTo learn about our staff, see here:<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/about-us/\">About Us</a>\n\n</section>','About The Instructor','','inherit','open','closed','','1113-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-24 15:59:51','2015-09-24 15:59:51','',1113,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1113-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1105,1,'2015-06-05 19:03:02','2015-06-05 19:03:02','','bg-footer','','inherit','open','closed','','bg-footer','','','2015-06-05 19:03:02','2015-06-05 19:03:02','',0,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/bg-footer.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1111,1,'2015-06-09 19:06:46','2015-06-09 19:06:46','',