1-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1480,1,'2015-06-10 14:43:18','2015-06-10 14:43:18','From the <a href=\"http://www.hamilton.ca/ProjectsInitiatives/TeamUpToCleanUp/\">City of Hamilton Team Up to Clean Up page:</a>\r\n<p align=\"left\">\"Tim Hortons Team Up to Clean Up Spring Blitz is a major city-wide community clean up event that coincides withEarth Day and the Great American Cleanup. This annual city-wide spring clean up event is coordinatedby City staff in partnership with Hamilton\'s <a href=\"http://www.hamilton.ca/ProjectsInitiatives/CleanCityStrategy/CCLC+Home.htm\">Clean City Liaison Committee</a>.Last year\'sTim Hortons Team Up to Clean Up Spring Blitz attracted more than 16,000 enthusiastic volunteer registrants<em>. </em>The Team Up to Clean Up Program gives you the tools and tips to work together to keep your neighbourhood clean and greenall year round. The program helps keep public places in your neighbourhood clean and safe for everyone\'s use. These areas includemunicipal properties, community parks, trails, parking lots, alleyways, streets and so much more.Get agroup together and create a clean team!\"</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">We at Kumon of Hamilton West End are putting a Kumon Clean Up Team together for Sunday, April 28, from 3-5 pm - see our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/631180166897096/\">Facebook event page here </a>to clean up nearby Beulah Park as well as at least part of Highland Park - it\'s a big job but if we have enough hands it will be a fun and productive community effort.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Are you doing anything similar in your neighbourhood?</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/team_up_web_pic.jpg\"><img id=\"i-1326\" class=\"size-full wp-image\" src=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/team_up_web_pic.jpg?w=650\" alt=\"Image\" /></a></p>','Kumon \"Team Up to Clean Up\"','','inherit','open','closed','','1318-revision-v1','','','2015-06-10 14:43:18','2015-06-10 14:43:18','',1318,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1318-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1555,1,'2015-09-22 14:58:05','2015-09-22 14:58:05','<h2>Introduction</h2>\r\nI have nearly 20 years experience as an extensively trained and certified professional instructor. I will guide your children through their work while also providing direction, support and encouragement. Through careful observation of each student and his or her work, I create a personalized at-home study plan which I am constantly updating in response to each student\'s actual results on a class by class basis, as well as in response to my assessment of progress being made at home.\r\n\r\nI have learned through working with hundreds of children of all ages and a wide range of abilities and personalities that it is vital that each assignment be completed and corrected in a timely manner to 100% within a designated time frame. Thus parents are strongly encouraged to check their children\'s work daily, and ensure corrections are done quickly and comfortably. Close adherence to the Kumon method has helped my students increase study skills, math and/or English skills as well as their self-confidence, and thus they become more self-reliant.\r\n\r\nI have a true passion for education and an earnest desire to help children succeed. I have seen how Kumon can transform lives for the better and know that while it demands a significant family commitment, it is well worth the investment of time and money.\r\n\r\n<section class=\"subSec\">\r\n<h2><span id=\"cphContent_ctl00_listSection_labelSectionTitle_1\">Biography and Background</span></h2>\r\n[circleimage imgurl=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/001-e1436885039303.jpg\" align=right has_hovericon=false]As a franchise owner and instructor , I ran learning centres in both French and English in the Outremont and West Island areas of Montreal before moving to Hamilton in the fall of 2010.\r\n\r\nHaving successfully guided hundreds of students in the Kumon method, I have made more than a career of it. It is a way of life for me. I have noticed that many people come to Kumon after trying different tutoring approaches and becoming discouraged with the lack of results. It is amazing how much of a difference Kumon can make to children\'s learning.\r\nAnother passion of mine is singing in classical concert choirs. I currently sing with Voces Animaeand the choir at the Anglican Church of the Ascension on John and Charlton, directed by John Laing - see his site at <a href=\"http://www.johnlaing.ca/\">http://www.johnlaing.ca/</a>. I am one of the main soloists and cantors at the church, and often play the flute there. I have formerly sung with Masterworks of Oakville.\r\n\r\nFinally, I am a member of the Hamilton Chamber of Commerce and the Canadian Federation of Independent Business (CFIB).\r\n\r\nTo learn about our staff, see here:<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/about-us/\">About Us</a>\r\n\r\n</section>','About The Instructor','','inherit','open','closed','','1113-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 14:58:05','2015-09-22 14:58:05','',1113,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1483,1,'2015-06-10 15:21:36','2015-06-10 15:21:36','','office','','inherit','open','closed','','office','','','2015-06-10 15:21:36','2015-06-10 15:21:36','',1069,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/office.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1484,1,'2015-09-22 15:14:17','2015-09-22 15:14:17','We celebrated our annual Awards ceremony for all our students on Tuesday, April 28, 2015, during our regular class hours of 3:30 to 7:00 p.m. The posters that summarize all awards may be seen on display in the study area at the centre.\n\nNow that autumn is here, we are completing the following summer contests:\n\n1) Summer Reading Challenge - the two students who read the most books in July and August, and write at least one paragraph on each book, i