hod has helped my students increase study skills, math and/or English skills as well as their self-confidence, and thus they become more self-reliant.\r\n\r\nI have a true passion for education and an earnest desire to help children succeed. I have seen how Kumon can transform lives for the better and know that while it demands a significant family commitment, it is well worth the investment of time and money.\r\n\r\n<section class=\"subSec\">\r\n<h2><span id=\"cphContent_ctl00_listSection_labelSectionTitle_1\">Biography and Background</span></h2>\r\n[circleimage imgurl=\"<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/001-e1436885039303.jpg\">http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/c3fa1662-ff06-485a-8533-03a578fa86ff.jpg\" </a>align=right has_hovericon=false]As a franchise owner and instructor , I ran learning centres in both French and English in the Outremont and West Island areas of Montreal before moving to Hamilton in the fall of 2010.\r\n\r\nHaving successfully guided hundreds of students in the Kumon method, I have made more than a career of it. It is a way of life for me. I have noticed that many people come to Kumon after trying different tutoring approaches and becoming discouraged with the lack of results. It is amazing how much of a difference Kumon can make to children\'s learning.\r\nAnother passion of mine is singing in classical concert choirs. I currently sing with Voces Animaeand the choir at the Anglican Church of the Ascension on John and Charlton, directed by John Laing. I am the primary soloist and cantor at the church. I have also sung with Masterworks of Oakville.\r\n\r\n</section>','About The Instructor','','inherit','open','closed','','1113-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 14:45:13','2015-07-14 14:45:13','',1113,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1485,1,'2015-06-10 15:43:15','2015-06-10 15:43:15','I am the owner/operator of the Kumon Math and Reading Centre of H