irection of renowned organist and composer John Laing - see his site at <a href=\"http://www.johnlaing.ca/\">http://www.johnlaing.ca/</a>','About','','inherit','open','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 15:28:07','2015-07-14 15:28:07','',2,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1511,1,'2015-09-22 13:47:13','2015-09-22 13:47:13','Our Math programis carefully designed to help support your child in study at the \"just-right\" level for him or her, beginning with a comfortable, confident starting point, to prepare for success in high school, university and beyond.\n\nEach level has 200 worksheets. Practice is provided based on the individual needs of the child, and the number of worksheets used daily is also individualised.\n\nLevels 7A-4A are the Early Learner levels, where students develop basic numeracy skills through 50.\n\nLevels 3A-B are the addition and subtraction levels. This is where most Kumon students begin their studies with us, developing a strong foundation of addition and subtraction fact memorization, and the ability to do vertical addition and subtraction with regrouping at a mastery level.\n\nLevels C-D are the multiplication and division levels, providing students with very strong mental calculation skills in short and long multiplication and division, as well as teaching them how to convert improper fractions to mixed numbers and how to reduce fractions.\n\nLevels E-F are the operations with fractions and decimals levels which are so necessary for success with algebra and calculcus. We do the thorough groundwork in fractions most students lack through schoolwork.\n\nLevels G-I are the basic algebra levels, which also cover negative numbers, exponents, and graphing skills, the core concepts of grades 7 through grade 11.\n\nLevels J-O are the advanced algebra and calculus levels.\n\nLevels X are the enrichment modules for high school students studying in levels J-O who wish to delve deeper into topics like vectors, matrices, probability and statistics.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Math','','inherit','open','closed','','1504-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-22 13:47:13','2015-09-22 13:47:13','',1504,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1504-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1512,1,'2015-07-14 15:38:16','2015-07-14 15:38:16','Our Math programme is carefully designed to help support your child in study at the \"just-right\" level for him or her, from a comfortable, confident starting point to prepare for success in high school, university and beyond.\r\n\r\nEach level has 200 worksheets. Practice is provided based on the individual needs of the child, and the number of worksheets used daily is also individualised.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A-4A are the Early Learner levels, where students develop basic numeracy skills through 50.\r\n\r\nLevels 3A-B are the addition and subtraction levels where most Kumon students begin developing a strong foundation of addition and subtraction fact memorisation and the ability to do vertical addition and subtraction with regrouping at a mastery level.\r\n\r\nLevels C-D are the multiplication and division levels, providing students with very strong mental calculation skills in short and long multiplication and division as well as converting improper fractions to mixed numbers and reducing fractions.\r\n\r\nLevels E-F are the operations with fractions and decimals levels which prepare students for success with algebra and calculcus.\r\n\r\nLevels G-I are the basic algebra levels, which also cover negative numbers, exponents, and graphing skills from the core concepts of grades 7-8 through grade 11.\r\n\r\nLevels J-O are the advanced algebra and calculus levels.\r\n\r\nLevels X are the enrichment modules for high school students studying in levels J-O who wish to delve deeper into topics like vectors, matrices, probability and statistics.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Math','','inherit','open','closed','','1504-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 15:38:16','2015-07-14 15:38:16','',1504,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1504-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1513,1,'2015-07-14 15:57:31','2015-07-14 15:57:31','The Kumon Reading program is a highly effective approach to developing strong reading comprehension and structural writing skills through materials which cover topics and stories from countries all over the world and a very enriched vocabulary.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A-3A are the Early Learner levels, where students gain the necessary sight word base to read simple texts comfortably as well as excellent phonics and decoding skills. For more details about these levels, see<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/early-learners/\">here.</a>\r\n\r\nLevels 2A-CII are the basic grammar, reading comprehension, and vocabulary development levels, approximately covering the primary grades in the Ontario curriculum, where students become fluent in reading and proficient in basic sentence analysis (nouns/verbs/adjectives/adverbs and subject/predicate/direct object), and working with commonly used verb tenses as well as the passive and active voice. The wide variety of engaging stories used here is mostly fiction.\r\n\r\nLevels DI-FII correspond approximately to middle school material in the Ontario curriculum, and incorporate much more non-fiction, as well as more and more advanced vocabulary, reading comprehension, and elements of writing to prepare fully for high school.\r\n\r\nLevels G-L correspond approximately to high school material in the Ontario curriculum, exploring high-level reading comprehension, summary, summation, prcis, and critical analysis of advanced materials including classical poetry and Shakespeare. The vocabulary level here is extremely high, providing an excellent preparation for success in university and beyond.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Reading','','publish','open','closed','','reading','','','2015-10-21 02:18:29','2015-10-21 02:18:29','',0,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/?page_id=1513',0,'page','',0),(1514,1,'2015-07-14 15:57:31','2015-07-14 15:57:31','The Kumon Reading programme is a highly effective approach to develop strong reading comprehension and structural writing skills through materials which cover topics and stories from countries all over the world and a very enriched vocabulary.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A-3A are the Early Learner levels, where students develop the necessary sight word base to read simple texts comfortably as well as excellent phonics and decoding skills.\r\n\r\nLevels 2A-CII are the basic grammar, reading comprehension, and vocabulary development levels, from approximately grades 1-5 levels, where students become fluent in reading and proficient in basic sentence analysis (nouns/verbs/adjectives/adverbs and subject/predicate/direct object), and working with commonly used verb tenses as well as the passive and active voice. The wide variety of engaging stories used here are many fiction.\r\n\r\nLevels DI-FII correspond approximately to middle school material in the Ontario curriculum, and incorporate much more non-fiction, as well as more and more advanced vocabulary, reading comprehension, and elements of writing to prepare fully for high school.\r\n\r\nLevels G-L correspond approximately to high school material in the Ontario curriculum, exploring high level reading comprehension, summary, summation, precis, and critical analysis of advanced materials including classical poetry and Shakespeare. The vocabulary level here is extremely high, providing an excellent preparation for success in university and beyond.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Reading','','inherit','open','closed','','1513-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 15:57:31','2015-07-14 15:57:31','',1513,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1513-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1515,1,'2015-07-14 16:22:22','2015-07-14 16:22:22','\"How early is early learning in Kumon? If my child is 2 or 3, is she too young for Kumon?\"\r\n\r\nThe only way to know for sure if your child is ready for Kumon is to bring her or him in for a free placement test at the centre. Generally, we have found 2 year old children do not usually have the patience to sit and study daily for at least 15-20 minutes, and advise that you begin around 3 or 4, depending on the personality and patience of your child with focused seat work.\r\n\r\nIf a child is not quite ready, we will usually recommend to re-test in 3-6 months. Often by that time, the child has become eager and prepared to begin learning Kumon.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A and 6A of the Reading program, and 6A and 5A of the Math program, are designed to help young children not only develop strong pre-reading and basic numeracy skills, but also begin to develop study skills that will stand them in good stead throughout their life - good pencil hold, good posture, fine-motor skills, neatness of presentation, concentration/focus and the facility to study steadily instead of being constantly distracted, and so on.\r\n\r\nIn 5A through 3A of Reading and 4A and early 3A of Math, students prepare for the big transition to the main study area of Kumon where they will be developing more and more independent study skills at a pace comfortable for each child.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Early Learners','','publish','open','closed','','early-learners','','','2015-10-21 02:18:29','2015-10-21 02:18:29','',0,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/?page_id=1515',0,'page','',0),(1516,1,'2015-07-14 16:22:22','2015-07-14 16:22:22','\"How early is an early learning in Kumon? If my child is 2 or 3, is she too young for Kumon?\"\r\n\r\nThe only way to know for sure if your child is ready for Kumon is to bring her or him in for a free placement test at the centre. Generally, we have found 2 year old children do not usually have the patience to sit and study daily for at least 15-20 minutes, and advise that you begin around 3 or 4, depending on the personality and patience of your child with focused seat work.\r\n\r\nIf a child is not quite ready, we will usually recommend to re-test in 3-6 months. Often by that time, the child has become eager and prepared to begin learning Kumon.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A and 6A of the Reading programme, and 6A and 5A of the Math programme, are designed to help young children not only develop strong pre-reading and basic numeracy skills, but also begin to develop study skills that will stand them in good stead throughout their life - good pencil hold, good posture, fine-motor skills, neatness of presentation, concentration/focus and the facility to study steadily instead of being constantly distracted, and so on.\r\n\r\nIn 5A through 3A of Reading and 4A and early 3A of Math, students prepare for the big transition to the main study area of Kumon where they will be developing more and more independent study skills at a pace comfortable for each child.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Early Learners','','inherit','open','closed','','1515-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 16:22:22','2015-07-14 16:22:22','',1515,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1515-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1517,1,'2015-07-14 17:08:26','2015-07-14 17:08:26','<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>Testimonial #1</h2>\r\n<h3>Alex and Kaiets Story</h3>\r\nAlex and Kaiet are twins who enrolled in Kumon Reading in June 2013, then added Math in April 2014. They are currently studying at a level more than 2 years advanced beyond their school grade in Reading, and nearly 2 years beyond their school grade in Math.\r\n\r\nLet\'s hear from their mother, Emilia:\r\n\r\n\"My father sent me a very interesting article about the wonders of Kumon and when I found the centre (within walking distance of our home), I decided to bring both boys. One of them could not sit still and had difficulties staying in one job for more than 5 minutes and I knew Kumon could help with that.\r\n\r\n\"I have seen huge improvements both at school and at home. They both have excellent working habits and are really ahead of their class in both reading and math.\"\r\n\r\nOther activities the boys enjoy: \"Swimming, skating, cycling, playing video games, doing experiments of all sorts, etc.\"\r\n\r\nAdvice for someone considering Kumon: \"Kumon will not only improve their reading and math but also will teach them how to develop good working habits. I also believe Kumon makes children feel confident in their abilities and lets them \'own\' their own process.\"\r\n\r\n\"After having my children enrolled in Kumon for two years, I have come to the conclusion that all kids should do Kumon from the earliest age possible. The benefits are so great that no parent should have any doubts about enrolling his/her children in Kumon when they are still young.\"\r\n\r\nTo read more success stories from centres all over North America, visit<a href=\"http://www.Facebook.com/Kumon\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.Facebook.com/Kumon</a>','Success Stories','','inherit','open','closed','','1120-revision-v1','','','2015-07-14 17:08:26','2015-07-14 17:08:26','',1120,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1518,1,'2015-07-14 17:10:36','2015-07-14 17:10:36','<h2>Testimonial #1</h2>\r\n<h3>Alex and Kaiets Story</h3>\r\nAlex and Kaiet are 7 year-old twins who enrolled in Kumon Reading in June 2013, then added Math in April 2014. They are currently studying at a level more than 2 years advanced beyond their school grade in Reading, and nearly 2 years beyond their school grade in Math.\r\n\r\nLet\'s hear from their mother, Emilia:\r\n\r\n\"My father sent me a very interesting article about the wonders of Kumon and when I found the centre (within walking distance of our home), I decided to bring both boys. One of them could not sit still and had difficulties staying in one job for more than 5 minutes and I knew Kumon could help with that.\r\n\r\n\"I have seen huge improvements both at school and at home. They both have excellent working habits and are really ahead of their class in both reading and math.\"\r\n\r\n<em>Other activities the boys enjoy:</em> \"Swimming, skating, cycling, playing video games, doing experiments 