the Canadian Federation of Independent Business (CFIB).\r\n\r\nTo learn about our staff, see here:http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/about-us/\r\n\r\n</section>','About The Instructor','','inherit','open','closed','','1113-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 14:56:46','2015-09-22 14:56:46','',1113,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1558,1,'2015-09-22 15:11:37','2015-09-22 15:11:37','Our Math programis carefully designed to help support your child in study at the \"just-right\" level for him or her, beginning with a comfortable, confident starting point, to prepare for success in high school, university and beyond.\r\n\r\nEach level has 200 worksheets. Practice is provided based on the individual needs of the child, and the number of worksheets used daily is also individualized.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A-4A are the Early Learner levels, where students develop basic numeracy skills through 50. For more details about these levels, see<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/early-learners/\">here.</a>\r\n\r\nLevels 3A-B are the addition and subtraction levels. This is where most Kumon students begin their studies with us, developing a strong foundation of addition and subtraction fact memorization, and the ability to do vertical addition and subtraction with regrouping at a mastery level.\r\n\r\nLevels C-D are the multiplication and division levels, providing students with very strong mental calculation skills in short and long multiplication and division, as well as teaching them how to convert improper fractions to mixed numbers and how to reduce fractions.\r\n\r\nLevels E-F are the operations with fractions and decimals levels which are so necessary for success with algebra and calculcus. We do the thorough groundwork in fractions most students lack through schoolwork.\r\n\r\nLevels G-I are the basic algebra levels, which also cover negative numbers, exponents, and graphing skills, the core concepts of grades 7 through grade 11.\r\n\r\nLevels J-O are the advanced algebra and calculus levels.\r\n\r\nLevels X are the enrichment modules for high school students studying in levels J-O who wish to delve deeper into topics like vectors, matrices, probability and statistics.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Math','','inherit','open','closed','','1504-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 15:11:37','2015-09-22 15:11:37','',1504,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1504-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1559,1,'2015-09-22 15:12:36','2015-09-22 15:12:36','The Kumon Reading program is a highly effective approach to developing strong reading comprehension and structural writing skills through materials which cover topics and stories from countries all over the world and a very enriched vocabulary.\r\n\r\nLevels 7A-3A are the Early Learner levels, where students gain the necessary sight word base to read simple texts comfortably as well as excellent phonics and decoding skills. For more details about these levels, see<a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/early-learners/\">here.</a>\r\n\r\nLevels 2A-CII are the basic grammar, reading comprehension, and vocabulary development levels, approximately covering the primary grades in the Ontario curriculum, where students become fluent in reading and proficient in basic sentence analysis (nouns/verbs/adjectives/adverbs and subject/predicate/direct object), and working with commonly used verb tenses as well as the passive and active voice. The wide variety of engaging stories used here is mostly fiction.\r\n\r\nLevels DI-FII correspond approximately to middle school material in the Ontario curriculum, and incorporate much more non-fiction, as well as more and more advanced vocabulary, reading comprehension, and elements of writing to prepare fully for high school.\r\n\r\nLevels G-L correspond approximately to high school material in the Ontario curriculum, exploring high-level reading comprehension, summary, summation, prcis, and critical analysis of advanced materials including classical poetry and Shakespeare. The vocabulary level here is extremely high, providing an excellent preparation for success in university and beyond.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Reading','','inherit','open','closed','','1513-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 15:12:36','2015-09-22 15:12:36','',1513,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1513-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1561,1,'2015-09-22 15:17:19','2015-09-22 15:17:19','We celebrated our annual Awards ceremony for all our students on Tuesday, April 28, 2015, during our regular class hours of 3:30 to 7:00 p.m. The posters that summarize all awards may be seen on display in the study area at the centre.\r\n\r\nNow that autumn is here, we are completing the following summer contests:\r\n\r\n1) Summer Reading Challenge - the two students who read the most books in July and August, and write at least one paragraph on each book, in two different age categories (7 and under, 8 and up), will win the opportunity to purchase a book of their choice, up to a value of $30.\r\n\r\n2) Weekly Raffles - variety of prizes available in centre -now that we are settling into the fall routine, students have opportunities to submit raffle tickets for keeping up twice a week with getting homework checked and recorded on their trackers. Good study skills build strong self-learners.\r\n\r\n3) Level Up!Students who were enrolled during July, August and/or September will receive ballots for entry into a contest to win one of three $20 Chapters gift cards at the centre. Students earned additional ballots by moving on to a new level and by reaching or maintaining a spot on the Advanced Student Honour Roll.There will also be two Grand Prize Winners in our Toronto West branch who will each receive an iPad Mini provided by Kumon Canada!\r\n\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------','News/Gallery','','inherit','open','closed','','568-revision-v1','','','2015-09-22 15:17:19','2015-09-22 15:17:19','',568,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/568-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1562,1,'2015-09-23 13:17:59','2015-09-23 13:17:59','<h3>Kumon of Hamilton West End</h3>\r\n[circleimage has_hovericon=false hovericon=fa-chevron-circle-right class=\"alignright\" imgurl=http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/001-e1436885039303.jpg] Centre Director and Instructor, Nicole Smith, has 20 years experience running Kumon centres in Montreal and Ontario, working in both French and English. She has through her Kumon centres helped many hundreds of students over these years develop in their math, English, and learning skills, including her own three children, all of whom are successfully pursuing careers and university studies in Montreal.\r\n\r\nOur staff:\r\n\r\n1) Our receptionist, Holly Fraser, has worked the longest of all the staff at the centre, and has become very knowledgeable about the Kumon programs and how best to help children get a good start and make excellent progress at the centre.\r\n\r\n2) Our Early Learners assistant, Roshaya Rodness, worked for several years at a Montreal centre with emergent readers and is highly effective at facilitating the development of each student according to his or her particular needs.\r\n\r\n3) Math and Reading staff: Elizabeth Selinger, Sara Manzoor, Ananya Sharma, Nuzhat Rafique, and Clair Macauley-Newcombe.\r\n\r\n[spacer]\r\n<h3></h3>','About Us','','inherit','open','closed','','211-revision-v1','','','2015-09-23 13:17:59','2015-09-23 13:17:59','',211,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/211-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1564,1,'2015-09-23 13:23:14','2015-09-23 13:23:14','We celebrated our annual Awards ceremony for all our students on Tuesday, April 28, 2015, during our regular class hours of 3:30 to 7:00 p.m. The posters that summarize all awards may be seen on display in the study area at the centre.\r\n\r\nNow that autumn is here, we are completing the following summer contests:\r\n\r\n1) Summer Reading Challenge - the two st