fluenced by a Sensing Thinking parent) may behave like an ISTP.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://psychologyjunkie.com/2015/09/17/the-childhood-struggles-of-every-myers-briggs-type/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1584\" src=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/childhood-struggles-mbti.jpg\" alt=\"childhood-struggles-mbti\" width=\"851\" height=\"410\" /></a>','Children and MBTI Personality Characteristics','One of my hobbies, along with singing and playing the flute, is delving into the intricacies of Myers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI). I belong to Facebook groups where we explore the parameters, joys, and challenges of the 16 types, especially the four Intuitive Feeling types (NFs).\r\n\r\nThis week, I found an excellent article on how children from the 16 types experience MBTI. If you follow our frequently-updated Facebook page, you may have noticed my post about it. (Don\'t follow us on Facebook and wish to? Click here. To read the full article by Susan Storm, see here. If you are not familiar with MBTI and are curious to see what type you might be (or your children might be), see here.\r\n\r\nSusan\'s article is quite long, but very much worth reading. If you already know what type you or your child is, you may simply scroll down to find what she says about the challenges of the type.\r\n\r\nWhat I am discovering as I study MBTI and the functional stack each type has is that the more you truly and deeply understand a person\'s personality, through MBTI, the Enneagram types, or other means, the easier it becomes to navigate the sometimes tempest-tossed waters of a whole variety of relationships with others ','inherit','open','closed','','1583-revision-v1','','','2015-10-29 18:52:40','2015-10-29 18:52:40','',1583,'http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/1583-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1597,1,'2016-02-01 22:45:33','2016-02-01 22:45:33','February:\r\n\r\nMy recent business trip to Malaysia - blogged here:https://kumonofhamiltonwestend.wordpress.com/2016/02/01/malaysia/\r\n\r\nJanuary:\r\n\r\nGet the latest details about our rescheduled Open House in March, scheduling progress updates about your child, and how to maximize your referral bonuses when you encourage your friends to join Kumon.\r\n\r\nhttp://eepurl.com/bOF1Cr\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"templateContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td id=\"templateBody\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextContentContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"600\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextContent\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Sailing Into September Newsletter 2015</strong><a href=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Boys-dive-into-the-Medite-008.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1574\" src=\"http://kumonofhamiltonwestend.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Boys-dive-into-the-Medite-008.jpg\" alt=\"Boys dive into the Mediterranean from Cleopatra\'s Rock, on the Egyptian coast 500km north of Cairo.\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHas September felt like diving into the unknown ocean rather than sailing into the sunset? Autumn can be a very challenging season, especially for families with lots of activities on their plate.\r\n\r\nPerhaps <strong>checking your child\'s homework</strong> feels like one extra challenging item? Consider:\r\n\r\n1) It takes as little as<strong> 2-5 minutes per day.</strong>\r\n2) It can make the difference between your child stalling in Kumon because the same mistakes are repeated every day (or worse, worksheets are being skipped or completed carelessly), or your child progressing smoothly and beautifully.\r\n3) Without it, your child can get the impression that Kumon is not really important to you. After all, your child must do 20 minutes or more of work 7 days a week on Kumon. If you do not even give 2 minutes a day to support your child\'s work, it doesn\'t look like you value their efforts.\r\n4) Your child gets<strong> instant positive feedback</strong> when the work is perfect, or close to perfect. How great is that for a warm glow and motivation to keep doing a good job?\r\n5) Our <strong>weekly raffle draws</strong> are now based on all homework being checked and entered on the homework tracker. If you don\'t check the homework, your child misses out on those fun draws.\r\n\r\nOur <strong>answer books</strong> make checking work very quick and easy. If you need an answer book or any guidance with how to do it and correctly enter results on the homework tracker, simply ask Holly at the reception desk the next time you are at Kumon. She will be more than happy to assist you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextContentContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"600\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextContent\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<h1>LevelUp Ballots</h1>\r\nDepending on how many months your children have been in the program, whether they are doing both math and reading, whether they have just attained a new Advanced Honour Roll level, or how many levels they have completed in the past three months, they may receive between one and 10 or more ballots to possibly win a Chapters gift card.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td id=\"templateColumns\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table class=\"columnWrapper\" border=\"0\" width=\"300\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpaddin